Yayin da kasar Sin ke kara bunkasa ayyukan kere kere, Amurka na bukatar ninka kudaden da take kashewa a wannan fannin, in ji Kai-Fu Lee, wani dan kasuwa da ke aiki a fannin kere kere, wanda ya yi aiki a Google, Microsoft da Apple.
Wannan ra'ayi ya zo ne bayan da yawancin sassan gwamnatin Amurka suka yi magana game da fasaha; duk da cewa Amurka gabaɗaya ba ta da wata manufa game da fasaha.
A halin yanzu, kasar Sin ta kaddamar da shirinta a bara: tana da burin zama kasa ta farko a fannin kere-kere a shekarar 2030.
Lee ya ce: "Nuna ninki biyu na kudaden da ake kashewa a binciken AI zai zama kyakkyawan farawa, saboda sauran ƙasashe suna da nisa a baya ga Amurka kuma muna neman hanyar isa ga manyan fasahohin AI".
Sau biyu tallafin zai ninka damar samun manyan ayyukan fasaha a Amurka, Lee ya fada wa CNBC a wannan makon.
Lee, marubucin littafin "AI Superpowers: China, Silicon Valley and the New World Order" wanda Houghton Mifflin Harcourt ya wallafa a wannan watan, shine Shugaba na Sinovation Ventures, wani kamfani da ya saka hannun jari a manyan kamfanonin kere kere na kasar Sin, Face++.
A shekarun 1980 a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon, ya kirkiro wata hanyar da za ta iya amfani da hankali na wucin gadi don wucewa da ɗan wasan kwaikwayo na Amurka Othello, wanda daga baya ya zama Shugaba na Microsoft Research da shugaban Google na China.
Lee ya amince da gasar fasaha ta gwamnatin Amurka kamar gasar Robotics Challenge ta Hukumar Kula da Ci gaban Nazarin Harkokin Tsaro kuma an tambaye shi lokacin da za a gudanar da gasar gaba don taimakawa gano masu fasaha na gaba.
Lee ya ce masu bincike a Amurka suna aiki tukuru don samun tallafin gwamnati.
Lee ya ce, "Ba wai kawai kasar Sin za ta kori malamai masu basira ba, amma za ta kori kamfanoni".
Facebook, Google da sauran kamfanonin fasaha sun ɗauki manyan masana jami'a don yin aiki a kan ayyukan ilimin kere kere a cikin fewan shekarun da suka gabata.
