"Yanzu kasar Sin ta kara tsaurara matakan hana ta shiga harkar kasuwanci da kuma sanya tallace-tallace masu tayar da hankali a cikin jaridunmu masu zaman kansu", in ji Branstad a wata sanarwa da jaridar Des Moines Register ta wallafa a ranar Lahadi.
Branstad ya ce: "Domin fadada ikon mallakar ta, gwamnatin China tana amfani da al'adun Amurka na 'yancin magana da' yancin 'yan jarida ta hanyar sanya tallace-tallace da aka biya a jaridar Des Moines Register".
"A wani bangare kuma, a kan gidajen sayar da jaridu a titunan Beijing, za ka ga maganganun masu nuna rashin jin dadin gwamnati amma ba za ka ga ainihin hoton ra'ayoyi daban-daban ba cewa kasar Sin na iya fuskantar matsalar tattalin arziki saboda kafofin yada labarai suna karkashin kulawar jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin", in ji shi.
